cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT

The paper discusses game theory and its connection to theoretical computer science and logic, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on extensive strategy profiles and coinduction techniques makes cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) the most likely category. The use of formalism and logic also suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as a possible category. Additionally, the mention of rational agents and their strategies could place the paper in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of information theory could make cs.IT (Information Theory) a relevant category as well.
